1
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:45,587
For more than a year, ominous rumours
had been privately circulating...

2
00:00:45,628 --> 00:00:48,090
among high-level Western leaders...

3
00:00:48,132 --> 00:00:52,011
that the Soviet Union had been at work
on what was darkly hinted to be...

4
00:00:52,094 --> 00:00:55,765
the ultimate weapon:
a doomsday device.

5
00:00:55,848 --> 00:00:59,770
Intelligence sources traced the site
of the top-secret Russian project...

6
00:00:59,811 --> 00:01:02,522
to the perpetually
fog-shrouded wasteland...

7
00:01:02,606 --> 00:01:05,984
below the Arctic peaks
of the Zhokhov Islands.

8
00:01:06,068 --> 00:01:11,407
What they were building or why it was
located in a remote, desolate place...

9
00:01:11,491 --> 00:01:13,743
no one could say.

10
00:03:44,033 --> 00:03:45,536
General Ripper, sir.

11
00:03:45,577 --> 00:03:47,538
Group Captain Mandrake speaking.

12
00:03:47,579 --> 00:03:49,581
This is General Ripper speaking.

13
00:03:49,665 --> 00:03:51,834
- Yes, sir.
- Do you recognise my voice?

14
00:03:51,917 --> 00:03:54,337
I do, sir. Why do you ask?

15
00:03:54,379 --> 00:03:56,172
Why do you think?

16
00:03:56,214 --> 00:03:59,843
I don't know, sir. We spoke
just a few moments ago, didn't we?

17
00:03:59,884 --> 00:04:05,141
You don't think I'd ask unless it was
pretty damned important, do you?

18
00:04:05,224 --> 00:04:06,642
No, I don't.

19
00:04:06,726 --> 00:04:08,894
Let's see if we can stay on the ball.

20
00:04:09,854 --> 00:04:12,440
Has the Wing confirmed holding
at their fail-safe points?

21
00:04:12,523 --> 00:04:15,360
Yes, sir. The confirmations
have just come in.

22
00:04:15,402 --> 00:04:19,031
Very well.
Now, listen to me carefully.

23
00:04:19,114 --> 00:04:21,908
The base is being put on condition red.

24
00:04:21,992 --> 00:04:24,203
I want this flashed
to all sections immediately.

25
00:04:24,287 --> 00:04:27,623
Condition red. Jolly good.
Keeps the men on their toes.

26
00:04:27,707 --> 00:04:29,959
This is not an exercise.

27
00:04:31,044 --> 00:04:32,920
Not an exercise?

28
00:04:34,590 --> 00:04:39,219
I shouldn't tell you this, but you're
a good officer and have a right to know.

29
00:04:39,303 --> 00:04:41,263
It looks like we're in a shooting war.

30
00:04:42,264 --> 00:04:47,228
- Oh, hell. Are the Russians involved?
- That's all I've been told.

31
00:04:47,270 --> 00:04:52,067
It came in on the red phone. I'm gonna
follow orders and seal this base tight.

32
00:04:53,152 --> 00:04:56,697
Now, I want you to transmit Plan R...

33
00:04:56,781 --> 00:04:58,699
R for Robert, to the Wing.

34
00:04:58,783 --> 00:05:02,161
- plan R for Robert.
- Is it that bad, sir?

35
00:05:02,244 --> 00:05:04,748
- Looks like it's pretty hairy.
- Yes, sir.

36
00:05:04,790 --> 00:05:06,833
Plan R for Robert.

37
00:05:06,917 --> 00:05:10,253
Last and possibly most important...

38
00:05:10,295 --> 00:05:14,550
I want all privately owned radios
to be immediately impounded.

39
00:05:14,634 --> 00:05:18,554
They might be used to issue
instructions to saboteurs.

40
00:05:18,638 --> 00:05:21,474
As I previously arranged, Air Police
will have lists of all owners.

41
00:05:21,557 --> 00:05:25,562
I want every one collected
without exception.

42
00:05:25,646 --> 00:05:27,940
After you've done that,
report back to me.

43
00:05:55,053 --> 00:05:57,723
In order to guard against
surprise nuclear attack...

44
00:05:57,806 --> 00:06:01,226
America's Strategic Air Command
maintains...

45
00:06:01,309 --> 00:06:05,440
a large force of B-52 bombers
airborne 24 hours a day.

46
00:06:05,523 --> 00:06:10,403
Each B-52 can deliver
a nuclear bomb load of 50 megatons...

47
00:06:10,486 --> 00:06:15,492
equal to 16 times the total
explosive force of all the bombs...

48
00:06:15,576 --> 00:06:20,164
and shells used by all the armies
in World War II.

49
00:06:20,247 --> 00:06:23,376
Based in America,
the Airborne Alert Force...

50
00:06:23,418 --> 00:06:26,212
is deployed from the Persian Gulf
to the Arctic Ocean.

51
00:06:26,296 --> 00:06:29,090
But they have one geographical factor
in common.

52
00:06:29,174 --> 00:06:33,137
They are all two hours
from their targets inside Russia.

53
00:07:53,183 --> 00:07:56,145
Major Kong, I know you'll think
this is crazy...

54
00:07:56,228 --> 00:07:59,898
but I just got a message from base
over the C.R.M. 114.

55
00:08:00,984 --> 00:08:04,946
It decodes as Wing attack Plan R.
R for Romeo.

56
00:08:08,032 --> 00:08:12,329
Goldie, did you say
Wing attack Plan R?

57
00:08:12,371 --> 00:08:13,914
Yes, sir, I have.

58
00:08:17,710 --> 00:08:22,424
Goldie, how many times have
I told you guys that I don't want...

59
00:08:22,507 --> 00:08:24,426
horsing around on the airplane?

60
00:08:24,509 --> 00:08:26,762
I'm not horsing around.
That's how it decodes.

61
00:08:26,845 --> 00:08:29,514
I've been to one world fair,
a picnic...

62
00:08:29,556 --> 00:08:33,436
and a rodeo, and that's the stupidest
thing I heard over earphones.

63
00:08:33,519 --> 00:08:35,396
You sure you got today's code?

64
00:08:36,856 --> 00:08:37,940
Yes, sir.

65
00:08:38,024 --> 00:08:40,569
There's gotta be something wrong.

66
00:08:40,652 --> 00:08:43,030
Wait a second, I'm coming back.

67
00:09:17,484 --> 00:09:21,155
Maybe you'd better get
a confirmation from base.

68
00:09:21,239 --> 00:09:22,657
Yes, sir.

69
00:09:43,805 --> 00:09:46,391
Major Kong, is it possible
this is some kind of loyalty test?

70
00:09:46,474 --> 00:09:50,146
You know, give the go code and then
recall to see who would actually go?

71
00:09:50,187 --> 00:09:54,316
Ain't nobody ever got
the go code yet.

72
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,819
Old Ripper wouldn't be giving us
Plan R...

73
00:09:56,861 --> 00:09:59,489
unless them Ruskies had already
clobbered Washington...

74
00:09:59,573 --> 00:10:01,867
and a lot of other towns
with a sneak attack.

75
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:03,201
Yes, sir.

76
00:10:03,285 --> 00:10:05,787
Major Kong,
message from base confirmed.

77
00:10:10,626 --> 00:10:13,004
Well, boys, I reckon this is it.

78
00:10:14,046 --> 00:10:17,341
Nuclear combat toe-to-toe
with the Ruskies.

79
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:37,238
Boys, I ain't much of a hand
at making speeches.

80
00:10:38,699 --> 00:10:41,994
But I got a fair idea
that something doggone important...

81
00:10:42,078 --> 00:10:44,038
is going on back there.

82
00:10:44,121 --> 00:10:48,001
I've got a fair idea of the kind
of personal emotions...

83
00:10:48,085 --> 00:10:51,546
that some of you fellows
may be thinking.

84
00:10:51,588 --> 00:10:54,341
Heck, I reckon you wouldn't be
human beings...

85
00:10:54,424 --> 00:10:59,013
if you didn't have pretty strong
personal feelings about nuclear combat.

86
00:10:59,097 --> 00:11:02,016
I want you to remember one thing.

87
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:04,852
The folks back home
are counting on you.

88
00:11:04,936 --> 00:11:07,271
And by golly,
we ain't about to let them down.

89
00:11:08,607 --> 00:11:11,402
Tell you something else.

90
00:11:11,443 --> 00:11:16,448
If this thing turns out to be half
as important as I figure it might be...

91
00:11:16,532 --> 00:11:20,578
I'd say you're all in line
for some important promotions...

92
00:11:20,620 --> 00:11:24,457
and personal citations
when this thing's over with.

93
00:11:24,499 --> 00:11:27,294
That goes for every last one of you...

94
00:11:27,336 --> 00:11:31,173
regardless of your race,
colour or your creed.

95
00:11:31,257 --> 00:11:34,802
Now let's get this thing on the hump.
We got some flying to do.

96
00:11:48,443 --> 00:11:50,653
Buck, should I get it?

97
00:11:50,737 --> 00:11:52,655
Yeah, you'll have to.

98
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:00,372
Hello?

99
00:12:00,456 --> 00:12:05,043
Yes, General Turgidson is here,
but he can't come to the phone now.

100
00:12:05,127 --> 00:12:07,380
This is his secretary, Miss Scott.

101
00:12:08,506 --> 00:12:10,717
Freddie, how are you?

102
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:13,052
Fine. And you?

103
00:12:13,136 --> 00:12:17,808
Oh, we were just catching up
on some of the general's paperwork.

104
00:12:17,892 --> 00:12:22,521
He's tied up.
I'm afraid he can't come to the phone.

105
00:12:23,564 --> 00:12:25,024
Just a minute.

106
00:12:25,065 --> 00:12:28,361
General Turgidson,
a Colonel Puntrich calling.

107
00:12:28,403 --> 00:12:30,363
Tell him to call back.

108
00:12:30,405 --> 00:12:35,118
Freddie, the general says
could you call back in a minute?

109
00:12:35,202 --> 00:12:37,121
He says it can't wait.

110
00:12:37,205 --> 00:12:40,541
For Pete's...
Find out what he wants.

111
00:12:40,583 --> 00:12:44,504
The general is in the powder room
right now.

112
00:12:44,587 --> 00:12:46,840
Could you tell me what it's about?

113
00:12:48,258 --> 00:12:52,387
Just a second. Apparently they monitored
a transmission eight minutes ago...

114
00:12:52,429 --> 00:12:54,932
from Burpelson Air Force Base.

115
00:12:56,768 --> 00:13:01,856
Right. It was directed to
the 843rd Bomb Wing on airborne alert.

116
00:13:03,608 --> 00:13:07,071
It decoded as Wing attack Plan R.

117
00:13:07,154 --> 00:13:12,827
Well, tell him to call what's-his-name,
Base Commander Ripper.

118
00:13:12,910 --> 00:13:14,578
Do I have to think of everything?

119
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:19,251
The general suggests you call General
Ripper, the 843rd base commander.

120
00:13:19,292 --> 00:13:22,712
Oh. All communications are dead!

121
00:13:22,796 --> 00:13:26,175
Bull! Tell him to do it himself.

122
00:13:26,259 --> 00:13:31,180
The general asks if you could
possibly try again yourself.

123
00:13:31,264 --> 00:13:35,936
I see. He says he's tried personally
several times, but everything is dead.

124
00:13:35,978 --> 00:13:38,772
Even the normal phone lines
are shut down.

125
00:13:46,030 --> 00:13:48,867
Fred? Buck.
What's it look like?

126
00:13:50,493 --> 00:13:51,911
Yeah?

127
00:13:53,329 --> 00:13:56,333
Well, are you sure
it's Plan R?

128
00:13:57,585 --> 00:14:00,296
Huh. What's cooking
on the threat board?

129
00:14:00,337 --> 00:14:03,132
Nothing? Nothing at all?

130
00:14:05,343 --> 00:14:07,387
I don't like the look of this.

131
00:14:08,847 --> 00:14:11,475
Tell you what you better do,
old buddy.

132
00:14:11,558 --> 00:14:14,729
You better give Elmo and Charlie a blast
and bump everything up to condition red.

133
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:17,356
Stand by the blower.
I'll get back to you.

134
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,650
- What's up?
- Nothing.

135
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:24,531
- Where's my shorts?
- On the floor. Where are you going?

136
00:14:24,573 --> 00:14:26,325
No place.

137
00:14:26,408 --> 00:14:31,163
I thought I might mosey over to the
War Room to see what's doing over there.

138
00:14:31,205 --> 00:14:33,040
It's 3:00 in the morning.

139
00:14:33,082 --> 00:14:35,043
The air force never sleeps.

140
00:14:35,085 --> 00:14:39,047
Buck, honey, I'm not sleepy either.

141
00:14:41,716 --> 00:14:44,512
I know how it is, baby.

142
00:14:44,553 --> 00:14:46,597
Tell you what you do.

143
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:51,602
You start your countdown
and old Bucky will be back...

144
00:14:51,685 --> 00:14:55,232
before you can say "Blastoff!"

145
00:14:56,525 --> 00:15:00,612
Your Commie has no regard
for human life, not even his own.

146
00:15:01,780 --> 00:15:05,618
For this reason, men, I want
to impress upon you the need...

147
00:15:05,701 --> 00:15:07,787
for extreme watchfulness.

148
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:11,874
The enemy may come individually
or he may come in strength.

149
00:15:11,958 --> 00:15:14,545
He may even come in the uniform
of our own troops.

150
00:15:15,546 --> 00:15:18,132
But however he comes,
we must stop him.

151
00:15:18,215 --> 00:15:20,968
We must not allow him
to gain entrance to this base.

152
00:15:22,511 --> 00:15:26,433
Now, I am going to give you
three simple rules.

153
00:15:26,516 --> 00:15:31,020
First: Trust no one,
whatever his uniform or rank...

154
00:15:31,104 --> 00:15:33,566
unless he is known to you personally.

155
00:15:33,649 --> 00:15:36,527
Secondly: Anyone or anything...

156
00:15:36,610 --> 00:15:41,490
that approaches within 200 yards
of the perimeter is to be fired upon.

157
00:15:41,574 --> 00:15:47,205
Third: If in doubt, shoot first
and ask questions afterwards.

158
00:15:47,289 --> 00:15:50,625
I would sooner accept a few casualties
through accident...

159
00:15:50,709 --> 00:15:54,839
than lose the entire base
and its personnel through carelessness.

160
00:15:54,922 --> 00:15:59,051
Any variation on these rules
must come from me personally.

161
00:16:00,136 --> 00:16:02,973
Now, men, in conclusion...

162
00:16:03,015 --> 00:16:07,102
I would like to say
that in the two years...

163
00:16:07,186 --> 00:16:10,981
that it has been my privilege
to be your commanding officer...

164
00:16:11,023 --> 00:16:13,985
I have always expected
the best from you...

165
00:16:14,027 --> 00:16:17,947
and you have never given me
anything less than that.

166
00:16:18,031 --> 00:16:21,367
Today the nation is counting on us.

167
00:16:22,452 --> 00:16:25,289
We are not going to let them down.

168
00:16:25,372 --> 00:16:27,291
Good luck to you all.

169
00:16:57,491 --> 00:17:00,035
Here's the attack profile, sir.

170
00:17:27,774 --> 00:17:30,444
This is your attack profile.

171
00:17:30,527 --> 00:17:33,614
"To ensure that the enemy cannot monitor
voice transmission...

172
00:17:33,698 --> 00:17:35,867
or plant false transmission...

173
00:17:35,950 --> 00:17:41,080
the C.R.M. 114 is to be switched
into all receiver circuits.

174
00:17:41,122 --> 00:17:44,585
The emergency base code prefix
is to be set...

175
00:17:44,668 --> 00:17:47,087
on the dials of the C.R.M.

176
00:17:47,129 --> 00:17:51,718
This will block any transmission other
than those preceded by a code prefix."

177
00:17:53,303 --> 00:17:55,430
Stand by to set code prefix.

178
00:17:55,513 --> 00:17:57,974
Roger. Ready to set code prefix.

179
00:17:58,057 --> 00:17:59,934
"Set code prefix."

180
00:18:09,487 --> 00:18:10,905
Code prefix set.

181
00:18:10,989 --> 00:18:12,616
"Lock code prefix."

182
00:18:15,327 --> 00:18:16,745
Code prefix locked.

183
00:18:16,828 --> 00:18:20,290
"Switch all receiver circuits
to C.R.M. discriminators."

184
00:18:21,501 --> 00:18:24,754
Switched to C.R.M. discriminators.

185
00:18:24,837 --> 00:18:26,672
"Check auto destruct circuits."

186
00:18:30,009 --> 00:18:31,929
Auto destruct circuits checked.

187
00:18:37,351 --> 00:18:41,731
"Primary target:
the I.C.B.M. complex at Laputa.

188
00:18:41,815 --> 00:18:46,027
Target reference:
Yankee, golf, tango...

189
00:18:46,111 --> 00:18:48,154
3-6-0.

190
00:18:48,238 --> 00:18:50,198
Thirty megaton nuclear device...

191
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:54,370
fused for air burst at 10,000 feet.

192
00:18:54,411 --> 00:18:58,916
Twenty megaton nuclear device
will be used if first malfunctions.

193
00:18:58,999 --> 00:19:01,670
Otherwise, proceed to secondary target:

194
00:19:01,711 --> 00:19:05,757
missile complex seven miles east
of Borchov.

195
00:19:05,841 --> 00:19:09,803
Target reference:
November, bravo, Xray...

196
00:19:09,886 --> 00:19:12,348
1-0-8.

197
00:19:12,431 --> 00:19:17,728
Fused air burst at 10..."
Check..."12,000 feet."

198
00:19:29,032 --> 00:19:32,912
Excuse me, sir. Something rather
interesting has just cropped up.

199
00:19:32,996 --> 00:19:35,832
Listen to that. Music.
Civilian broadcasting.

200
00:19:37,459 --> 00:19:41,714
I think the Pentagon has given us
an exercise to check our readiness.

201
00:19:41,797 --> 00:19:43,757
I think it's taking things too far.

202
00:19:43,841 --> 00:19:46,886
Our fellows will be inside Russian
radar cover in about 20 minutes.

203
00:19:46,969 --> 00:19:50,182
Listen. Chock full of stations
all churning it out.

204
00:19:51,975 --> 00:19:53,727
- Mandrake?
- Yes, sir?

205
00:19:53,810 --> 00:19:57,230
I issued instructions for all radios
to be impounded.

206
00:19:57,314 --> 00:20:01,611
You did, and I was in the process of
impounding this when I switched it on.

207
00:20:01,652 --> 00:20:05,156
I thought our fellows hitting Russian
radar, dropping all their stuff...

208
00:20:05,239 --> 00:20:09,703
I'd better tell you because if they do,
it'll cause a stink.

209
00:20:09,787 --> 00:20:13,832
Group Captain,
the officer exchange program...

210
00:20:13,916 --> 00:20:17,544
does not give you any special
prerogatives to question my orders.

211
00:20:17,628 --> 00:20:21,841
I realise that, sir, but I thought
you'd be pleased to hear the news.

212
00:20:21,925 --> 00:20:24,677
After all, let's face it.

213
00:20:24,761 --> 00:20:28,765
We don't want to start a nuclear war
unless we have to, do we?

214
00:20:29,725 --> 00:20:33,395
Please sit down.
And turn that thing off.

215
00:20:33,479 --> 00:20:34,605
Yes, sir.

216
00:20:34,688 --> 00:20:39,569
What about the planes? Surely we must
issue the recall code immediately.

217
00:20:39,653 --> 00:20:42,531
The planes are not going
to be recalled.

218
00:20:42,572 --> 00:20:45,450
My attack orders have been issued,
and the orders stand.

219
00:20:47,494 --> 00:20:51,666
If you'll excuse me for saying so,
that would be to my way of thinking...

220
00:20:51,707 --> 00:20:53,876
rather an odd way of looking at it

221
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:56,379
If a Russian attack was in progress...

222
00:20:56,420 --> 00:21:00,384
we would certainly not be hearing
civilian broadcasting.

223
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:03,303
- Are you certain?
- I'm absolutely positive.

224
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:06,098
What if it is true?

225
00:21:06,181 --> 00:21:09,185
I'm afraid I'm still not with you, sir,
because I mean...

226
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:13,148
if a Russian attack
was not in progress...

227
00:21:13,231 --> 00:21:17,569
then your use of Plan R... In fact,
your orders to the entire Wing...

228
00:21:25,077 --> 00:21:30,333
I would say, sir, that there was
something dreadfully wrong somewhere

229
00:21:31,418 --> 00:21:33,753
Why don't you take it easy,
Group Captain?

230
00:21:33,837 --> 00:21:36,506
Please make me a drink
of grain alcohol and rainwater...

231
00:21:36,590 --> 00:21:39,010
and help yourself
to whatever you'd like.

232
00:21:48,061 --> 00:21:52,149
General Ripper, sir, as an officer
in Her Majesty's Air Force...

233
00:21:52,232 --> 00:21:55,486
it is my clear duty
under the present circumstances...

234
00:21:55,569 --> 00:22:00,241
to issue the recall code upon my
own authority and bring back the Wing.

235
00:22:00,325 --> 00:22:02,327
If you'll excuse me, sir.

236
00:22:10,961 --> 00:22:15,841
Sir, I must ask you for the key and the
recall code. Have you got them handy?

237
00:22:15,925 --> 00:22:18,428
I told you to take it easy,
Group Captain.

238
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:21,056
There's nothing anybody can do now.

239
00:22:21,139 --> 00:22:23,558
I'm the only person who knows
the three-letter code group.

240
00:22:23,642 --> 00:22:26,186
I must insist
that you give them to me!

241
00:22:35,279 --> 00:22:39,284
Do I take it, sir, you are threatening
a brother officer with a gun?

242
00:22:40,536 --> 00:22:45,666
Mandrake, I suppose
it never occurred to you...

243
00:22:45,749 --> 00:22:49,337
that while we're chatting here
so enjoyably...

244
00:22:49,420 --> 00:22:53,299
a decision is being made
by the president...

245
00:22:53,383 --> 00:22:56,511
and the joint chiefs in the War Room
at the Pentagon.

246
00:22:57,596 --> 00:23:03,185
When they realise there is
no possibility of recalling the Wing...

247
00:23:03,269 --> 00:23:07,566
there will be only one course
of action open.

248
00:23:07,649 --> 00:23:09,526
Total commitment.

249
00:23:11,820 --> 00:23:16,241
Mandrake, do you recall what
Clemenceau once said about war?

250
00:23:17,535 --> 00:23:20,246
No, I don't think I do, sir. No.

251
00:23:21,914 --> 00:23:24,959
He said war was too important
to be left to the generals.

252
00:23:26,043 --> 00:23:30,632
When he said that 50 years ago...

253
00:23:30,716 --> 00:23:32,676
he might have been right.

254
00:23:32,718 --> 00:23:35,095
But today...

255
00:23:35,179 --> 00:23:38,641
war is too important
to be left to politicians.

256
00:23:38,725 --> 00:23:43,188
They have neither the time,
the training...

257
00:23:43,271 --> 00:23:46,317
nor the inclination
for strategic thought.

258
00:23:49,945 --> 00:23:53,449
I can no longer sit back
and allow...

259
00:23:53,532 --> 00:23:58,705
Communist infiltration,
Communist indoctrination...

260
00:23:58,788 --> 00:24:00,415
Communist subversion...

261
00:24:01,875 --> 00:24:05,755
and the international
Communist conspiracy...

262
00:24:05,796 --> 00:24:08,674
to sap and impurify...

263
00:24:08,758 --> 00:24:12,094
all of our precious
bodily fluids.

264
00:24:18,268 --> 00:24:19,770
Staines, is everybody here?

265
00:24:19,812 --> 00:24:22,314
Mr. President, the secretary of state
is in Vietnam.

266
00:24:22,397 --> 00:24:26,361
The secretary of defence is in Laos, and
the vice president is in Mexico City.

267
00:24:26,444 --> 00:24:31,407
We can establish contact with them at
anytime. The undersecretaries are here.

268
00:24:31,491 --> 00:24:34,577
Right. General Turgidson,
what's going on?

269
00:24:36,121 --> 00:24:38,666
Mr. President...

270
00:24:38,749 --> 00:24:42,419
about 35 minutes ago...

271
00:24:42,503 --> 00:24:46,466
General Jack Ripper,
the commanding general...

272
00:24:46,550 --> 00:24:49,010
of Burpelson Air Force Base...

273
00:24:49,052 --> 00:24:52,347
issued an order to the 34 B-52s
of his Wing...

274
00:24:52,389 --> 00:24:54,516
which were airborne at the time...

275
00:24:54,599 --> 00:24:58,729
as part of a special exercise we were
holding called Operation Dropkick.

276
00:24:58,813 --> 00:25:03,484
It appears that the order
called for the planes...

277
00:25:03,568 --> 00:25:06,947
to attack their targets
inside Russia.

278
00:25:07,030 --> 00:25:11,243
The planes are fully armed
with nuclear weapons...

279
00:25:11,326 --> 00:25:14,831
with an average load
of 40 megatons each.

280
00:25:14,914 --> 00:25:19,377
The central display of Russia will
indicate the position of the planes.

281
00:25:20,879 --> 00:25:24,090
The triangles
are their primary targets.

282
00:25:24,174 --> 00:25:27,094
The squares
are their secondary targets.

283
00:25:28,179 --> 00:25:33,476
The aircraft will begin penetrating
Russian radar cover within 25 minutes.

284
00:25:35,687 --> 00:25:38,982
General Turgidson, I find this
very difficult to understand.

285
00:25:39,065 --> 00:25:44,322
I understood I was the only one
to order the use of nuclear weapons.

286
00:25:45,448 --> 00:25:49,535
That's right, sir. You are
the only person authorised to do so.

287
00:25:49,619 --> 00:25:53,916
And although I hate to judge
before all the facts are in...

288
00:25:53,999 --> 00:25:57,628
it's beginning to look like
General Ripper exceeded his authority.

289
00:25:57,711 --> 00:26:02,591
It certainly does, far beyond the point
I would have imagined possible.

290
00:26:02,633 --> 00:26:06,262
Perhaps you're forgetting
the provisions of Plan R, sir.

291
00:26:06,346 --> 00:26:08,181
Plan R?

292
00:26:09,599 --> 00:26:13,144
Plan R is an emergency war plan...

293
00:26:13,228 --> 00:26:15,731
in which a lower echelon commander
may order...

294
00:26:15,815 --> 00:26:18,943
nuclear retaliation
after a sneak attack...

295
00:26:19,026 --> 00:26:22,530
if the normal chain of command
has been disrupted.

296
00:26:22,613 --> 00:26:25,492
You approved it, sir.
You must remember.

297
00:26:27,035 --> 00:26:30,872
Surely you must recall, sir,
when Senator Beaufort made...

298
00:26:30,956 --> 00:26:33,918
that big hassle about our deterrent
lacking credibility.

299
00:26:34,001 --> 00:26:38,714
The idea was for Plan R to be
a sort of retaliatory safeguard.

300
00:26:38,798 --> 00:26:40,758
A safeguard?

301
00:26:40,842 --> 00:26:44,137
I admit the human element seems
to have failed us here.

302
00:26:44,179 --> 00:26:47,599
But the idea was to discourage
the Ruskies from any hope...

303
00:26:47,683 --> 00:26:52,271
they could knock out Washington, and
yourself, as part of a sneak attack...

304
00:26:52,354 --> 00:26:56,526
and escape retaliation because of lack
of proper command and control.

305
00:26:56,609 --> 00:26:59,320
I assume the planes will return
automatically...

306
00:26:59,362 --> 00:27:01,406
once they reach their fail-safe points.

307
00:27:02,532 --> 00:27:07,037
I'm afraid not. The planes were holding
at their fail-safe points...

308
00:27:07,121 --> 00:27:09,123
when the go code was issued.

309
00:27:09,206 --> 00:27:13,712
Once they fly beyond fail-safe, they do
not require a second order to proceed.

310
00:27:13,795 --> 00:27:15,714
They will continue
until they reach their target.

311
00:27:15,797 --> 00:27:18,842
Then why haven't you radioed the planes,
countermanding the go code?

312
00:27:20,552 --> 00:27:23,556
We're unable to communicate
with any of the aircraft.

313
00:27:23,639 --> 00:27:25,850
Why?

314
00:27:25,892 --> 00:27:28,311
As you may recall, sir...

315
00:27:28,394 --> 00:27:32,023
one of the provisions
of Plan R provides...

316
00:27:32,064 --> 00:27:36,695
that once the go code
is received...

317
00:27:36,737 --> 00:27:40,073
the normal S.S.B. radios
in the aircraft...

318
00:27:40,157 --> 00:27:42,619
are switched into
a special coded device...

319
00:27:42,702 --> 00:27:45,747
which I believe is designated
as C.R.M. 114.

320
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:50,251
In order to prevent the enemy
from issuing fake or confusing orders...

321
00:27:50,335 --> 00:27:54,256
C.R.M. 114 is designed
not to receive at all...

322
00:27:54,340 --> 00:27:59,887
unless the message is proceeded by the
correct three-letter code group prefix.

323
00:27:59,929 --> 00:28:05,310
You mean to tell me you will be unable
to recall the aircraft?

324
00:28:05,393 --> 00:28:08,313
That's the size of it.
However, we are ploughing through...

325
00:28:08,396 --> 00:28:11,274
every possible three-letter combination
of the code.

326
00:28:11,358 --> 00:28:16,572
But since there are
17,000 permutations...

327
00:28:16,614 --> 00:28:20,243
it's going to take us about two
and a half days to transmit them all.

328
00:28:20,284 --> 00:28:23,080
How soon will the planes penetrate
Russian radar cover?

329
00:28:23,121 --> 00:28:26,625
- About 18 minutes from now.
- Are you in contact with General Ripper?

330
00:28:26,708 --> 00:28:31,631
No, sir. General Ripper sealed off
the base and cut off communications.

331
00:28:31,673 --> 00:28:33,299
Where did you get this information?

332
00:28:33,383 --> 00:28:36,970
General Ripper called
Strategic Air Command Headquarters...

333
00:28:37,053 --> 00:28:39,597
shortly after he issued the go code.

334
00:28:39,639 --> 00:28:43,269
I have a portion of the conversation
transcript if you'd like me to read it.

335
00:28:43,352 --> 00:28:45,145
Read it.

336
00:28:46,939 --> 00:28:49,692
The duty officer asked
General Ripper...

337
00:28:49,775 --> 00:28:53,029
to confirm the fact that he had
issued the go code and he said:

338
00:28:54,030 --> 00:28:58,326
"Yes, gentlemen, they are on their way
in and no one can bring them back.

339
00:28:58,410 --> 00:29:01,205
For the sake of our country
and our way of life...

340
00:29:01,289 --> 00:29:03,958
I suggest you get the rest of SAC
in after them.

341
00:29:04,041 --> 00:29:08,963
Otherwise, we will be totally destroyed
by Red retaliation.

342
00:29:09,005 --> 00:29:14,344
My boys will give you the best kind
of start: 1,400 megatons worth.

343
00:29:14,386 --> 00:29:17,973
And you sure as hell
won't stop them now.

344
00:29:18,015 --> 00:29:20,894
So let's get going.
There's no other choice.

345
00:29:20,977 --> 00:29:25,857
God willing, we will prevail
in peace and freedom from fear...

346
00:29:25,899 --> 00:29:29,319
and in true health
through the purity...

347
00:29:29,402 --> 00:29:33,240
and essence of our natural...

348
00:29:33,324 --> 00:29:34,742
fluids.

349
00:29:35,743 --> 00:29:37,745
God bless you all."

350
00:29:39,705 --> 00:29:42,334
Then he hung up.

351
00:29:42,375 --> 00:29:46,004
We're still trying to figure out
the meaning of that last phrase, sir.

352
00:29:46,046 --> 00:29:50,384
There's nothing to figure out.
This man is obviously a psychotic.

353
00:29:50,468 --> 00:29:55,556
I'd like to hold off judgment
until all the facts are in.

354
00:29:55,640 --> 00:30:00,229
General Turgidson, when you instituted
the human reliability tests...

355
00:30:00,312 --> 00:30:04,233
you assured me there was no possibility
of such a thing ever occurring.

356
00:30:06,235 --> 00:30:10,281
Well, I don't think it's fair
to condemn a whole program...

357
00:30:10,365 --> 00:30:13,034
because of a single slip up, sir.

358
00:30:13,076 --> 00:30:15,620
I want to speak to General Ripper
on the telephone.

359
00:30:15,703 --> 00:30:17,205
That's impossible.

360
00:30:17,288 --> 00:30:21,210
General Turgidson, I am becoming
less and less interested...

361
00:30:21,293 --> 00:30:24,839
in your estimates
of what is possible and impossible.

362
00:30:26,006 --> 00:30:27,424
General Faceman.

363
00:30:27,508 --> 00:30:28,676
Yes, sir?

364
00:30:28,759 --> 00:30:31,096
Are there any army units
stationed near Burpelson?

365
00:30:31,179 --> 00:30:33,223
I'll just check, sir.

366
00:30:38,103 --> 00:30:39,521
Hello?

367
00:30:41,107 --> 00:30:44,318
I told you never to call me here.
Don't you know where I am?

368
00:30:46,737 --> 00:30:49,407
Look, baby, I can't talk to you now.

369
00:30:49,491 --> 00:30:52,035
My president needs me.

370
00:30:52,119 --> 00:30:55,747
Of course Bucky would rather
be there with you.

371
00:30:56,832 --> 00:30:59,961
Of course it isn't only physical.

372
00:31:00,044 --> 00:31:02,505
I deeply respect you
as a human being.

373
00:31:02,589 --> 00:31:05,675
Someday I'm going to make you
Mrs. Buck Turgidson.

374
00:31:06,843 --> 00:31:09,805
Oh, listen, you go back to sleep.

375
00:31:09,847 --> 00:31:12,850
Bucky will be there as soon as he can.

376
00:31:12,892 --> 00:31:17,479
All right. Listen, don't forget
to say your prayers.

377
00:31:24,529 --> 00:31:28,450
Apparently,
the 23rd Airborne Division...

378
00:31:28,533 --> 00:31:31,329
is stationed seven miles away
at Alvarado.

379
00:31:31,412 --> 00:31:35,666
General Faceman, I want them to enter
the base, locate General Ripper...

380
00:31:35,750 --> 00:31:38,127
and put him in immediate
telephone contact with me.

381
00:31:38,211 --> 00:31:39,838
Yes, sir.

382
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,548
Mr. President?

383
00:31:41,632 --> 00:31:43,217
If I may advise.

384
00:31:43,300 --> 00:31:47,554
Under a condition red, it is standard
procedure that the base be sealed off...

385
00:31:47,638 --> 00:31:50,391
and the base defended
by base security troops.

386
00:31:50,475 --> 00:31:54,896
Any force trying to enter would
certainly encounter heavy casualties.

387
00:31:54,979 --> 00:31:59,026
General Turgidson, with all due respect
for your defence team...

388
00:31:59,109 --> 00:32:01,862
my boys can brush them aside
without too much trouble.

389
00:32:02,780 --> 00:32:07,535
Mr. President, there are one or two
points I'd like to make, if I may?

390
00:32:08,578 --> 00:32:10,038
Go ahead, General.

391
00:32:11,540 --> 00:32:16,211
One: Our hopes for recalling
the 843rd Bomb Wing...

392
00:32:16,253 --> 00:32:20,550
are quickly being reduced
to a very low order of probability.

393
00:32:20,633 --> 00:32:23,678
Two: In less than 15 minutes
from now...

394
00:32:23,761 --> 00:32:26,722
the Ruskies will be making
radar contact with the planes.

395
00:32:26,806 --> 00:32:28,809
Three: When they do...

396
00:32:28,892 --> 00:32:32,521
they will go absolutely ape and
strike back with everything they've got.

397
00:32:32,604 --> 00:32:36,483
Four: If prior to this time...

398
00:32:36,567 --> 00:32:40,029
we have done nothing to suppress
their retaliatory capabilities...

399
00:32:40,113 --> 00:32:43,741
we will suffer virtual annihilation.

400
00:32:46,828 --> 00:32:51,500
Five: If, on the other hand...

401
00:32:53,377 --> 00:32:58,717
we immediately launched an attack
on their airfields and missile bases...

402
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:01,970
we'd stand a damn good chance
of catching them with their pants down.

403
00:33:02,053 --> 00:33:04,431
Hell, we've got
a five-to-one missile superiority.

404
00:33:04,472 --> 00:33:07,267
We could easily assign three missiles
to every target...

405
00:33:07,309 --> 00:33:10,730
and still have a very effective reserve
force for any other contingency.

406
00:33:10,813 --> 00:33:16,152
Six: An unofficial study which
we undertook of this eventuality...

407
00:33:16,235 --> 00:33:21,158
indicated that we would destroy
90% of their nuclear capabilities.

408
00:33:21,241 --> 00:33:23,368
We would therefore prevail...

409
00:33:23,452 --> 00:33:26,663
and suffer only modest and acceptable
civilian casualties...

410
00:33:26,705 --> 00:33:31,169
from their remaining force which would
be badly damaged and uncoordinated.

411
00:33:31,211 --> 00:33:34,672
General, it is the avowed policy
of our country...

412
00:33:34,756 --> 00:33:36,926
never to strike first
with nuclear weapons.

413
00:33:37,009 --> 00:33:41,680
Well, Mr. President, General Ripper
has already invalidated that policy.

414
00:33:41,764 --> 00:33:46,185
That was not an act of national policy.
There are still alternatives open to us.

415
00:33:47,229 --> 00:33:52,025
Mr. President, we are rapidly
approaching a moment of truth...

416
00:33:52,108 --> 00:33:55,278
both for ourselves as human beings
and for the life of our nation.

417
00:33:55,362 --> 00:33:57,990
Truth is not always a pleasant thing.

418
00:33:58,074 --> 00:34:00,618
But it is necessary now
to make a choice:

419
00:34:00,701 --> 00:34:03,454
to choose between two admittedly
regrettable...

420
00:34:03,538 --> 00:34:07,000
but nevertheless distinguishable
postwar environments.

421
00:34:07,084 --> 00:34:11,880
One, where 20 million people are killed;
the other, 150 people killed.

422
00:34:11,922 --> 00:34:14,925
You're talking about mass murder,
General, not war.

423
00:34:14,967 --> 00:34:18,555
Mr. President, I'm not saying
we wouldn't get our hair mussed.

424
00:34:18,638 --> 00:34:23,268
But I do say no more than
10 to 20 million killed. Tops!

425
00:34:23,351 --> 00:34:25,353
Depending on the breaks.

426
00:34:25,436 --> 00:34:29,400
I will not go down in history as
the greatest mass murderer since Hitler!

427
00:34:29,483 --> 00:34:32,069
It might be better
if you were more concerned...

428
00:34:32,152 --> 00:34:35,489
with the American people than
with your image in the history books.

429
00:34:35,573 --> 00:34:38,577
General Turgidson,
I've heard quite sufficient from you.

430
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:41,079
Thank you very much.

431
00:34:41,121 --> 00:34:43,707
Mr. President, they have
the ambassador waiting upstairs.

432
00:34:43,790 --> 00:34:47,420
- Good. Any difficulty?
- He's having a fit about the M.P.s.

433
00:34:47,461 --> 00:34:49,964
That can't be helped.
Have him brought here straightaway.

434
00:34:50,006 --> 00:34:51,591
Yes, sir.

435
00:34:51,632 --> 00:34:54,176
Is that the Russian ambassador?

436
00:34:54,260 --> 00:34:56,346
Yes, it is, General.

437
00:34:58,473 --> 00:35:01,435
Am I to understand
the Russian ambassador...

438
00:35:01,476 --> 00:35:03,854
is to be admitted entrance
to the War Room?

439
00:35:03,937 --> 00:35:06,816
That is correct.
He is here on my orders.

440
00:35:09,694 --> 00:35:11,905
I don't know exactly how
to put this, sir...

441
00:35:11,988 --> 00:35:15,409
but are you aware of what a breach
of security that would be?

442
00:35:15,492 --> 00:35:19,622
He'll see everything.
He'll see the big board.

443
00:35:20,581 --> 00:35:22,917
That is precisely the idea, General.

444
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:25,211
That is precisely the idea.

445
00:35:26,755 --> 00:35:30,675
Staines, get Premier Kissoff
on the hot line.

446
00:35:37,808 --> 00:35:41,687
"Survival kit contents check.

447
00:35:41,771 --> 00:35:46,693
In them you will find
one .45 caliber automatic...

448
00:35:46,777 --> 00:35:49,279
two boxes of ammunition...

449
00:35:49,363 --> 00:35:52,616
four days concentrated
emergency rations...

450
00:35:52,699 --> 00:35:56,037
one drug issue
containing antibiotics...

451
00:35:56,079 --> 00:36:00,416
morphine, vitamin pills,
pep pills...

452
00:36:00,500 --> 00:36:04,295
sleeping pills,
tranquilliser pills...

453
00:36:04,379 --> 00:36:09,218
one miniature combination
Russian phrase book and Bible...

454
00:36:09,260 --> 00:36:12,304
$100 in roubles...

455
00:36:12,388 --> 00:36:14,516
$100 in gold...

456
00:36:14,558 --> 00:36:17,352
nine packs of chewing gum...

457
00:36:17,394 --> 00:36:19,354
one issue of prophylactics...

458
00:36:19,396 --> 00:36:23,441
three lipsticks,
three pair of nylon stockings."

459
00:36:23,525 --> 00:36:28,239
Shoot, a fellow could have a pretty
good weekend in Vegas with that stuff.

460
00:36:33,744 --> 00:36:36,623
- You don't have any fresh fish?
- I'm afraid not, sir.

461
00:36:36,707 --> 00:36:38,876
- Your eggs are fresh?
- Yes, sir.

462
00:36:38,959 --> 00:36:42,921
I will have poached eggs. And bring me
some cigars, please. Havana cigars.

463
00:36:43,005 --> 00:36:46,426
That will be all, sir?
I'll see to it right away.

464
00:36:46,467 --> 00:36:49,679
Try one of theseJamaican cigars,
Ambassador. They're good.

465
00:36:49,762 --> 00:36:53,224
Thank you, no. I do not support the work
of imperialist stooges.

466
00:36:53,308 --> 00:36:55,895
Oh, only Commie stooges, huh?

467
00:36:55,936 --> 00:36:57,521
Mr. President.

468
00:36:59,398 --> 00:37:02,693
You're gonna let that lousy Commie punk
vomit all over us like this?

469
00:37:02,776 --> 00:37:03,862
Mr. President?

470
00:37:03,945 --> 00:37:07,699
They haven't reached Premier Kissoff.
They don't know where he is...

471
00:37:07,782 --> 00:37:10,160
and he won't be back for two hours.

472
00:37:11,244 --> 00:37:13,748
Try B-8-6-5-4-3 Moscow.

473
00:37:13,831 --> 00:37:15,917
You would never have found him
through his office.

474
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:20,004
Our premier is a man of the people,
but he is also a man, if you follow.

475
00:37:20,087 --> 00:37:22,798
- Degenerate atheistic Commie.
- What did you say?

476
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:26,428
I said Premier Kissoff is
a degenerate atheistic Commie!

477
00:37:26,511 --> 00:37:29,431
- Have this ignorant fool...
- I'm sorry!

478
00:37:29,473 --> 00:37:33,436
Mr. President,
I think they're trying the number.

479
00:37:44,073 --> 00:37:47,201
Gentlemen, you can't fight in here.
This is the War Room!

480
00:37:47,284 --> 00:37:50,120
What is going on here?
I demand an explanation.

481
00:37:50,162 --> 00:37:54,459
This clumsy fool tried to plant
that ridiculous camera on me.

482
00:37:54,542 --> 00:37:57,128
You bet your sweets, Mr. Commie!
Look at this, Mr. President.

483
00:37:57,212 --> 00:38:00,799
This lousy Commie rat was taking
pictures with this of the big board!

484
00:38:01,883 --> 00:38:03,719
Mr. Ambassador!

485
00:38:03,803 --> 00:38:08,057
This clumsy fool attempted to plant
that ridiculous camera on me.

486
00:38:08,140 --> 00:38:11,018
That's a damn lie!
I saw him with my own eyes.

487
00:38:11,060 --> 00:38:15,274
This is outrageous. I have never heard
of such behaviour in the War Room before.

488
00:38:15,357 --> 00:38:17,818
Mr. President, I think
they're getting him on the line.

489
00:38:45,849 --> 00:38:47,767
You got to hand it to those Commies.

490
00:38:47,851 --> 00:38:52,398
Yeah. Those trucks sure look like
the real thing, don't they?

491
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:54,400
I wonder where they got them from.

492
00:38:54,442 --> 00:38:56,736
Probably bought them
from the army as war surplus.

493
00:39:00,448 --> 00:39:04,494
Okay, open up at 200 yards.

494
00:40:01,724 --> 00:40:05,395
Tell him where you are and that
you'll speak if I say anything untrue...

495
00:40:05,478 --> 00:40:07,772
but nothing more than that.

496
00:40:09,357 --> 00:40:12,778
Alexi? Alexi, please.
I beg you.

497
00:40:13,862 --> 00:40:16,448
But I don't have a phone.

498
00:40:16,532 --> 00:40:19,076
Give him the phone.

499
00:40:45,898 --> 00:40:50,235
I've done as you asked.
Be careful. I think he is drunk.

500
00:40:53,281 --> 00:40:57,702
Hello? Hello, Dimitri?

501
00:40:57,785 --> 00:41:00,205
Listen, I can't hear too well.

502
00:41:00,289 --> 00:41:03,542
Could you turn the music down
a little?

503
00:41:03,626 --> 00:41:05,544
That's much better.

504
00:41:05,586 --> 00:41:08,255
Yeah. Yeah.

505
00:41:09,506 --> 00:41:12,302
Fine. I can hear you now, Dimitri.

506
00:41:12,385 --> 00:41:15,889
Clear and plain
and coming through fine.

507
00:41:15,972 --> 00:41:20,353
I'm coming through fine, too, eh?
Good.

508
00:41:20,436 --> 00:41:24,398
Well, then, as you say,
we're both coming through fine. Good.

509
00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:26,400
It's good that you're fine...

510
00:41:26,484 --> 00:41:28,736
and I'm fine.

511
00:41:28,819 --> 00:41:32,032
I agree with you.
It's great to be fine.

512
00:41:32,950 --> 00:41:35,118
Now, Dimitri...

513
00:41:35,202 --> 00:41:40,917
you know how we've always talked
about the possibility...

514
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:43,670
of something going wrong
with the bomb.

515
00:41:45,046 --> 00:41:47,006
The bomb, Dimitri.

516
00:41:48,216 --> 00:41:50,844
The hydrogen bomb.

517
00:41:50,928 --> 00:41:53,889
Well, now, what happened is...

518
00:41:53,973 --> 00:41:58,185
one of our base commanders,
he had a sort of...

519
00:41:58,269 --> 00:42:01,481
Well, he went a little funny
in the head.

520
00:42:01,564 --> 00:42:04,651
You know, just a little funny.

521
00:42:04,734 --> 00:42:08,363
And he went and did a silly thing.

522
00:42:09,448 --> 00:42:11,367
I'll tell you what he did.

523
00:42:11,450 --> 00:42:13,786
He ordered his planes...

524
00:42:15,454 --> 00:42:17,915
to attack your country.

525
00:42:17,999 --> 00:42:20,377
Let me finish, Dimitri.

526
00:42:21,378 --> 00:42:23,380
Let me finish, Dimitri.

527
00:42:23,422 --> 00:42:26,633
Listen, how do you think
I feel about it?

528
00:42:26,717 --> 00:42:29,554
Can you imagine how I feel
about it, Dimitri?

529
00:42:31,097 --> 00:42:33,266
Why do you think I'm calling you?

530
00:42:33,349 --> 00:42:35,351
Just to say hello?

531
00:42:36,436 --> 00:42:38,856
Of course I like to speak to you!

532
00:42:38,897 --> 00:42:41,442
Of course I like to say hello!

533
00:42:41,525 --> 00:42:43,694
Not now, but anytime, Dimitri.

534
00:42:43,777 --> 00:42:47,823
I'm just calling up to tell you
something terrible has happened.

535
00:42:47,907 --> 00:42:50,869
Of course, it's a friendly call.

536
00:42:50,952 --> 00:42:55,206
Listen, if it wasn't friendly,
you probably wouldn't have even got it.

537
00:42:57,542 --> 00:43:02,298
They will not reach their targets
for at least another hour.

538
00:43:02,381 --> 00:43:05,468
I am positive, Dimitri.

539
00:43:05,551 --> 00:43:07,970
I've been all over this
with your ambassador.

540
00:43:08,054 --> 00:43:10,557
It is not a trick.

541
00:43:10,599 --> 00:43:12,100
I'll tell you.

542
00:43:12,142 --> 00:43:15,979
We'd like to give your Air Staff
a complete rundown on the targets...

543
00:43:16,063 --> 00:43:19,317
the flight plans
and defensive systems of the planes.

544
00:43:19,400 --> 00:43:24,322
Yes, if we're unable
to recall the planes...

545
00:43:24,405 --> 00:43:27,075
I'd say, well...

546
00:43:28,452 --> 00:43:32,831
we're just gonna have to help you
destroy them, Dimitri.

547
00:43:32,915 --> 00:43:35,834
I know they're our boys.

548
00:43:35,918 --> 00:43:38,421
Listen. Now, who should we call?

549
00:43:40,298 --> 00:43:44,761
Who should we call?
Sorry, you faded away.

550
00:43:45,971 --> 00:43:49,850
The Peoples Central
Air Defence Headquarters.

551
00:43:49,934 --> 00:43:52,228
Where is that, Dimitri?

552
00:43:52,311 --> 00:43:54,438
In Omsk. Right.

553
00:43:55,481 --> 00:43:56,774
Yes.

554
00:43:56,816 --> 00:43:59,736
You'll call them first, will you?

555
00:44:01,238 --> 00:44:04,157
Do you happen to have the phone number
on you, Dimitri?

556
00:44:06,034 --> 00:44:09,038
What? I see.
Just ask for Omsk information.

557
00:44:11,124 --> 00:44:15,253
I'm sorry too, Dimitri.
I'm very sorry.

558
00:44:15,336 --> 00:44:19,174
All right, you're sorrier than I am.
But I am sorry as well.

559
00:44:21,468 --> 00:44:23,721
I am as sorry as you are, Dimitri.

560
00:44:23,804 --> 00:44:25,764
Don't say that you're more sorry
than I am...

561
00:44:25,848 --> 00:44:28,768
because I'm capable of being
just as sorry as you are.

562
00:44:28,852 --> 00:44:30,770
So we're both sorry, all right?

563
00:44:30,854 --> 00:44:32,272
All right.

564
00:44:33,523 --> 00:44:37,778
Yes, he's right here. Yes, he wants
to talk to you. Just a second.

565
00:44:50,334 --> 00:44:52,044
What?

566
00:45:10,731 --> 00:45:13,567
What? What is it? What?

567
00:45:13,651 --> 00:45:16,696
The fools. The mad fools.

568
00:45:18,114 --> 00:45:20,241
What's happened?

569
00:45:20,325 --> 00:45:22,661
The doomsday machine.

570
00:45:22,744 --> 00:45:25,288
The doomsday machine?
What is that?

571
00:45:25,372 --> 00:45:30,795
A device which will destroy
all human and animal life on Earth.

572
00:45:30,836 --> 00:45:33,089
All human and animal life?

573
00:45:47,981 --> 00:45:50,275
- Mandrake?
- Yes, Jack?

574
00:45:51,567 --> 00:45:55,154
Have you ever seen a Commie
drink a glass of water?

575
00:45:55,238 --> 00:45:59,785
Well, I can't say I have, Jack.

576
00:46:00,995 --> 00:46:05,875
Vodka. That's what they drink,
isn't it? Never water.

577
00:46:05,959 --> 00:46:10,338
I believe that's what they drink, yes.

578
00:46:10,422 --> 00:46:13,883
On no account will a Commie
ever drink water...

579
00:46:13,967 --> 00:46:16,304
and not without good reason.

580
00:46:17,346 --> 00:46:20,016
Oh, yes.

581
00:46:20,099 --> 00:46:25,146
I can't quite see
what you're getting at.

582
00:46:26,315 --> 00:46:29,484
Water. That's what I'm getting at.
Water.

583
00:46:31,028 --> 00:46:34,489
Mandrake, water is the source
of all life.

584
00:46:36,034 --> 00:46:39,662
Seven-tenths of this Earth's surface
is water.

585
00:46:39,704 --> 00:46:43,041
Why, do you realise that...

586
00:46:43,124 --> 00:46:46,170
70% of you is water?

587
00:46:46,253 --> 00:46:47,713
Good Lord.

588
00:46:47,755 --> 00:46:52,885
And as human beings,
you and I need fresh, pure water...

589
00:46:52,968 --> 00:46:56,556
to replenish
our precious bodily fluids.

590
00:46:56,640 --> 00:46:59,392
- You beginning to understand?
- Yes.

591
00:47:06,734 --> 00:47:11,989
Have you never wondered why I drink
only distilled water...

592
00:47:12,073 --> 00:47:16,453
or rainwater,
and only pure grain alcohol?

593
00:47:16,536 --> 00:47:19,831
It did occur to me, Jack, yes.

594
00:47:20,916 --> 00:47:24,879
Have you ever heard of fluoridation
of water?

595
00:47:25,964 --> 00:47:29,801
Yes, I have heard of that, Jack, yes.

596
00:47:29,884 --> 00:47:31,803
Do you know what it is?

597
00:47:31,886 --> 00:47:35,015
No, no, I don't know what it is.

598
00:47:35,099 --> 00:47:39,019
Do you realise that fluoridation...

599
00:47:39,103 --> 00:47:41,939
is the most monstrously conceived...

600
00:47:41,981 --> 00:47:44,776
and dangerous Communist plot
we have ever had to face?

601
00:47:51,199 --> 00:47:53,159
Two can play at that game, soldier.

602
00:47:58,291 --> 00:48:01,002
That's nice shooting, soldier!

603
00:48:25,487 --> 00:48:27,531
Mandrake, come here.

604
00:48:27,615 --> 00:48:29,617
You calling me, Jack?

605
00:48:29,700 --> 00:48:32,161
Come over here
and help me with this belt.

606
00:48:35,206 --> 00:48:38,168
I haven't had very much experience...

607
00:48:38,251 --> 00:48:41,046
with those sort of machines.

608
00:48:41,129 --> 00:48:44,925
I've only ever pressed a button
in my old Spitfire.

609
00:48:45,009 --> 00:48:48,638
In the name of Her Majesty and the
Continental Congress, feed me this belt.

610
00:48:48,721 --> 00:48:53,477
Jack, I'd love to come,
but what's happened, you see...

611
00:48:53,560 --> 00:48:56,355
the string in my leg is gone.

612
00:48:57,397 --> 00:49:01,193
- The what?
- The string. I never told you.

613
00:49:01,276 --> 00:49:05,198
I've got a gammy leg.
Oh, dear. Gone. Shot off.

614
00:49:07,325 --> 00:49:10,995
Mandrake, come over here.
The redcoats are coming.

615
00:49:12,080 --> 00:49:16,251
When it is detonated, it will produce
enough radioactive fallout...

616
00:49:16,335 --> 00:49:18,253
so that in ten months...

617
00:49:18,337 --> 00:49:21,423
the surface of the Earth
will be as dead as the moon!

618
00:49:21,507 --> 00:49:24,469
Come on, De Sadesky!
That's ridiculous!

619
00:49:24,552 --> 00:49:28,682
Our studies show even the worst fallout
is down to a safe level after two weeks.

620
00:49:28,765 --> 00:49:33,771
- You never heard of cobalt theoium G.
- What about it?

621
00:49:33,854 --> 00:49:37,942
Cobalt thorium G has
a radioactive half-life of 93 years.

622
00:49:38,025 --> 00:49:41,112
If you take 50 H bombs
in the 100 megaton range...

623
00:49:41,195 --> 00:49:43,615
and jacket them
with cobalt thorium G...

624
00:49:43,657 --> 00:49:48,287
when they are exploded,
they will produce a doomsday shroud...

625
00:49:48,370 --> 00:49:50,664
a lethal cloud of radioactivity...

626
00:49:50,747 --> 00:49:55,169
which will encircle the Earth
for 93 years!

627
00:49:55,253 --> 00:49:58,798
What a load of Commie bull.
I mean, after all.

628
00:49:59,882 --> 00:50:02,553
I'm afraid I don't understand
something, Alexi.

629
00:50:02,636 --> 00:50:06,265
Is the premier threatening to explode it
if our planes carry out their attack?

630
00:50:06,307 --> 00:50:08,892
No, sir. It is not a thing
a sane man would do.

631
00:50:08,976 --> 00:50:11,896
The doomsday machine is designed
to trigger itself automatically.

632
00:50:11,980 --> 00:50:14,232
Surely you can disarm it somehow.

633
00:50:14,316 --> 00:50:18,236
It is designed to explode if
any attempt is made to un-trigger it.

634
00:50:18,320 --> 00:50:19,571
Automatically?

635
00:50:19,654 --> 00:50:22,241
It's a Commie trick!
We're wasting valuable time!

636
00:50:22,325 --> 00:50:25,411
Look at the big board!
They're getting ready to clobber us!

637
00:50:25,494 --> 00:50:30,124
This is absolute madness.
Why should you build such a thing?

638
00:50:30,207 --> 00:50:32,169
There are those of us
who fought against it.

639
00:50:32,252 --> 00:50:34,296
But in the end, we could not keep up
with the expense involved...

640
00:50:34,379 --> 00:50:38,925
in the arms race, the space race
and the peace race.

641
00:50:39,009 --> 00:50:44,223
At the same time, our people grumbled
for more nylons and washing machines.

642
00:50:44,307 --> 00:50:46,851
Our doomsday scheme cost us
just a small fraction...

643
00:50:46,934 --> 00:50:50,188
of what we have been spending on defence
in a single year.

644
00:50:50,229 --> 00:50:54,693
The deciding factor was when we learned
your country was working similarly...

645
00:50:54,735 --> 00:50:56,695
and we were afraid of a doomsday gap!

646
00:50:56,737 --> 00:51:00,115
This is preposterous! I've never
approved of anything like that.

647
00:51:00,199 --> 00:51:03,036
Our source was The New York Times.

648
00:51:03,078 --> 00:51:06,998
Dr. Strangelove, do we have anything
like that in the works?

649
00:51:07,040 --> 00:51:09,542
A moment, please, Mr. President.

650
00:51:12,254 --> 00:51:15,716
Under the authority granted me...

651
00:51:15,758 --> 00:51:19,929
as director of weapons research
and development...

652
00:51:20,012 --> 00:51:24,226
I commissioned last year
a study of this project...

653
00:51:24,267 --> 00:51:26,520
by the Bland Corporation.

654
00:51:26,603 --> 00:51:29,731
Based on the findings of the report...

655
00:51:29,815 --> 00:51:35,321
my conclusion was that this idea
was not a practical deterrent...

656
00:51:35,405 --> 00:51:39,242
for reasons which at this moment
must be all too obvious.

657
00:51:39,283 --> 00:51:42,705
You mean it is possible for them
to have built such a thing?

658
00:51:46,875 --> 00:51:51,756
Mr. President, the technology required
is easily within the means...

659
00:51:51,798 --> 00:51:56,219
of even the smallest nuclear power.

660
00:51:56,303 --> 00:52:00,224
It requires only the will to do so.

661
00:52:01,267 --> 00:52:05,104
But how is it possible for this thing
to be triggered automatically...

662
00:52:05,187 --> 00:52:07,523
and at the same time
impossible to un-trigger?

663
00:52:07,606 --> 00:52:11,611
Mr. President,
it is not only possible...

664
00:52:11,695 --> 00:52:13,655
it is essential.

665
00:52:13,697 --> 00:52:18,160
That is the whole idea
of this machine, you know.

666
00:52:18,201 --> 00:52:23,416
Deterrence is the art of producing
in the mind of the enemy...

667
00:52:23,499 --> 00:52:26,085
the fear of attack.

668
00:52:26,169 --> 00:52:31,091
And so because of the automated and
irrevocable decision-making process...

669
00:52:31,175 --> 00:52:35,054
which rules out human meddling...

670
00:52:35,137 --> 00:52:39,099
the doomsday machine is terrifying...

671
00:52:39,183 --> 00:52:41,269
and simple to understand...

672
00:52:41,353 --> 00:52:45,023
and completely credible
and convincing.

673
00:52:45,106 --> 00:52:48,443
I wish we had one of them
doomsday machines.

674
00:52:48,526 --> 00:52:52,114
But this is fantastic, Strangelove.
How can it be triggered automatically?

675
00:52:52,198 --> 00:52:55,993
It's remarkably simple to do that.

676
00:52:56,035 --> 00:52:59,581
When you merely wish to bury bombs...

677
00:52:59,665 --> 00:53:02,000
there's no limit to the size.

678
00:53:02,042 --> 00:53:04,294
After that, they are connected...

679
00:53:04,378 --> 00:53:08,382
to a gigantic complex of computers.

680
00:53:08,465 --> 00:53:14,180
Now then, a specific and clearly
defined set of circumstances...

681
00:53:14,263 --> 00:53:17,725
under which the bombs
are to be exploded...

682
00:53:17,809 --> 00:53:21,855
is programmed into a tape memory bank.

683
00:53:21,897 --> 00:53:25,025
Hmm. Strangelove?

684
00:53:26,068 --> 00:53:29,155
What kind of a name is that?
That ain't no Kraut name, is it?

685
00:53:29,239 --> 00:53:31,533
He changed it when he became a citizen.

686
00:53:31,574 --> 00:53:34,577
It used to be Merkwurdichliebe.

687
00:53:34,661 --> 00:53:39,041
Well, a Kraut by any other name,
uh, Stainsey?

688
00:53:40,918 --> 00:53:45,297
The whole point of
the doomsday machine...

689
00:53:45,381 --> 00:53:48,927
is lost if you keep it a secret!

690
00:53:49,011 --> 00:53:51,179
Why didn't you tell the world?

691
00:53:51,263 --> 00:53:55,642
It was to be announced
at the Party Congress on Monday.

692
00:53:55,726 --> 00:53:59,063
As you know,
the premier loves surprises.

693
00:54:47,532 --> 00:54:49,786
Stay with me, Mandrake.

694
00:54:54,957 --> 00:54:57,670
All right, now feed me.
Feed me, boy.

695
00:55:27,536 --> 00:55:32,582
Don't you think we'd be better off
away from this flying glass?

696
00:55:32,666 --> 00:55:34,710
We're okay here.

697
00:55:36,378 --> 00:55:40,383
Mandrake, do you realise that
in addition to fluoridating the water...

698
00:55:40,466 --> 00:55:44,053
there are studies underway
to fluoridate salt, flour...

699
00:55:44,095 --> 00:55:49,143
fruit juices, soup, sugar,
milk, ice cream?

700
00:55:49,226 --> 00:55:50,477
Ice cream.

701
00:55:50,561 --> 00:55:52,980
- Children's ice cream.
- Good Lord.

702
00:55:53,063 --> 00:55:55,482
You know when fluoridation
first began?

703
00:55:56,525 --> 00:55:58,445
No, I don't, Jack.

704
00:55:58,528 --> 00:56:00,989
1946.

705
00:56:01,072 --> 00:56:03,825
1946, Mandrake.

706
00:56:03,908 --> 00:56:08,205
How does that coincide with
your postwar Commie conspiracy, huh?

707
00:56:08,289 --> 00:56:11,584
It's incredibly obvious, isn't it?

708
00:56:11,625 --> 00:56:17,174
A foreign substance is introduced
into our precious bodily fluids...

709
00:56:17,257 --> 00:56:20,510
without the knowledge
of the individual.

710
00:56:20,594 --> 00:56:22,512
Certainly without any choice.

711
00:56:24,306 --> 00:56:27,643
That's the way a hard -core Commie works.

712
00:56:29,062 --> 00:56:32,273
Jack. Tell me, Jack.

713
00:56:32,357 --> 00:56:35,026
When did you first become...

714
00:56:35,109 --> 00:56:37,863
Well, develop this theory?

715
00:56:38,989 --> 00:56:41,200
Well, l...

716
00:56:41,283 --> 00:56:44,828
I first became aware of it, Mandrake...

717
00:56:44,912 --> 00:56:46,915
during the physical act of love.

718
